.\" -*- nroff -*-
.\" $Id$
.Dd Jan, 2005
.Os
.Dt ZILE 1
.Sh NAME
.Nm zee
.Nd Zee Is Lossy Emacs
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm zee
.Op Fl hqV
.Op Fl u Ar rcfile
.Op Ar +number
.Op Ar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm Zee
is another Emacs clone.
Zee is a customizable, self-documenting real-time
display editor.
.Pp
This document contains only a brief description of the Zee editor.  For a
more complete documentation, please read the Info file or the
Texinfo manual.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar +number
For the first file the cursor will be positioned on the line specified by
.Ar number
(do not insert a space between the "+" sign and the number).
.It Fl q
Do not load the user's initialization file.
.It Fl u Ar rcfile
Specify an alternate initialization file.
.It Fl V
Print version information on standard output then exit.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Fl
.It Pa ~/.zee
user customized Zee initialization file
.It Pa @pkgdatadir@/AUTODOC
self-documentation
.It Pa @pkgdatadir@/FAQ
Zee FAQ
.It Pa @pkgdatadir@/HELP
Zee manual
.It Pa @pkgdatadir@/TUTORIAL
Zee tutorial
.It Pa @pkgdatadir@/dotzee.sample
sample Zee initialization file
.El
